c: 3
v: 106
t: "This shall be on the day when countenances speak different languages; some being effulgent with splendour and bright light, beaming with joy and hope while others are dark and gloomy. Rebuked for want of faith, they shall be told: \"How could you deny Allah after you have recognized Him. You have well deserved to be put to the torment in requital of infidelity"